[normal]We also understand t
[normal]hat the Committee has received 
[normal]evidence 
[normal]submitted by 
[normal]the Foundation that summarises t
[normal]he main findings of the 
[normal]report.
[normal] RAC 
[normal]regards the report as 
[normal]fair and accurate and 
[normal]commend
[normal]s
[normal] it to the Committee. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]As part of the 
[normal]research conducted
[normal] for
[normal] this report, RAC patrols provided feedback on their own experience delivering service during the period January to March 2013 when the worst of the 2012/13 winter conditions were experienced. Specifically:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The report also states: “
[normal]Within 
[normal]free text comments
[normal] 
[normal]that also made up the response, 
[normal]there were
[normal] 
[normal]several observations that drivers appeared not to have heeded weather warnings and had been caught out, or unprepared, and that many of the stranded vehicles were not suitable for driving in the 
[normal]extreme weather 
[normal]conditions. There were also concerns about p
[normal]oor driving and lack of experience/skills for the 
[normal]road 
[normal]conditions. There were a large number of comments about the number of potholes in all types of road, and the observation that they are particularly dangerous when it has snowed, because they cannot be 
[normal]seen.
[normal]”
